canonical:
  title: 乞辭表
  author: 金克己
  language: lzh
  text: 伏以聖人無心從人所欲王事靡盬已事而竣瞻依穆穆之容控愬慺慺之意中謝 陪臣肅將邦貢來覘國光久辱舘居之燕安頻蒙臺餽之優厚帝恩加等雖知感慨以忘還君命告成故冒嚴明而乞退伏望俯回睿慮曲徇微誠優垂曰可之音俾遂言旋之計令臣等某月幾日朝辭某月幾日離舘歸國則湖山千里縱催窮日之行象魏九門長結望雲之戀
  rtl: true
  vertical: true
lzh_formatted:
  title: 乞辭表
  author: 金克己
  language: lzh
  text: 伏以聖人無心。從人所欲。王事靡盬。已事而竣。瞻依穆穆之容。控愬慺慺之意。中謝。 陪臣肅將邦貢。來覘國光。久辱舘居之燕安。頻蒙臺餽之優厚。帝恩加等。雖知感慨以忘還。君命告成。故冒嚴明而乞退。伏望俯回睿慮。曲徇微誠。優垂曰可之音。俾遂言旋之計。令臣等某月幾日朝辭。某月幾日離舘歸國。則湖山千里。縱催窮日之行。象魏九門。長結望雲之戀。
korean:
  title: 걸사표
  author: 김극기
  language: kor
  text: 엎드려 생각하옵건대, 성인(聖人)은 사심이 없사와 남의 하고픈 바를 들어주고, 왕사(王事)는 견고하지 못하였으나 자신의 일은 이미 마쳤습니다. 씩씩하신 용모를 우러러 바라옵고 공근한 뜻을 호소하옵니다. 중사(中謝) 배신은 삼가 본국의 조공을 받들고 와서 황국의 광휘(光輝)를 구경하옵고, 오랫동안 편안히 사관에 머물면서 자주 관으로부터 후한 선물을 받았사온데, 황제의 은혜가 등수(等數)를 더하시어 비록 감격하여 돌아갈 생각을 잊을 만도 하오나, 임금의 명령을 완수하였기로 위엄을 모독하고 물러갈 것을 청하옵니다. 엎드려 바라건대, 성려(聖慮)를 굽어 돌이키시어 미미한 정성에 응종하시고 그러하겠다는 윤음을 특별히 내리시어 돌아갈 계획을 완수하게 하심과 동시에 신 등으로 하여금 모월 모일에 하직하고, 모월 모일에 사관을 떠나 본국으로 돌아가게 하여 주시오면, 호산(湖山)이라 천릿길에 비록 해가 저물도록 갈 길을 재촉할 것이오며, 대궐의 구문(九門)이 길이 구름을 바라는 그리움을 맺겠사옵니다.
  url: https://db.itkc.or.kr/dir/item?itemId=BT#dir/node?dataId=ITKC_BT_1365A_0450_010_0120&viewSync=OT
  footnotes: []
english:
  title: A Petition for Leave to Depart
  author: Kim Geuk-gi
  language: eng
  text: |-
    I humbly bow and speak: The sage possesses no selfish heart, thus fulfilling the desires of others. Though the affairs of state remain unfinished, my own duties are complete. I gaze upward with reverence at your dignified countenance, and present before you my earnest plea.

    Your humble servant has dutifully brought tribute from our homeland and come to behold the radiance of your imperial throne. For long I have dwelt in comfort within these halls, repeatedly blessed by your generous gifts. The Emperor's grace has multiplied beyond measure—so much so that gratitude has made me forget the longing for home. Yet my lord's command is fulfilled, and so I humbly dare to request permission to withdraw.

    I earnestly beseech you: turn your wise deliberation toward this petition, and grant your favor to this humble sincerity. Grant me your gracious assent, that I may complete my journey homeward. Let your servant bid farewell on such-and-such a day of such-and-such a month, and depart these halls on such-and-such a day of such-and-such a month to return to our land. Then, though the lakes and mountains stretch a thousand leagues ahead and the days grow short, I shall hasten my steps. And before the nine gates of the palace, I shall forever cherish the longing gaze toward the clouds.
  footnotes:
  - key: ''
    value: This is a formal petition (표, 'pyo') written by a Korean envoy requesting permission to return home after his diplomatic mission was complete.
  - key: ''
    value: The 'nine gates' (구문) refer to the gates of the Chinese imperial palace, symbolizing the grandeur and majesty of the court.
  - key: ''
    value: The imagery of gazing at clouds expresses the perpetual longing and reverence the envoy will maintain for the imperial court even after returning home.
